New constructor — store created externally, passed to both KanbanContext and StateManager:
```rust
pub fn new(save_file: Option<String>) -> KanbanResult<(Self, ...)> {
    let (store, state_manager, save_rx, completion_rx) = if let Some(ref path) = save_file {
        let store = kanban_service::make_store(path)?;
        let (sm, rx, crx) = StateManager::new(Some(store.clone()))?;
        (Some(store), sm, Some(rx), Some(crx))
    } else { ... };
    let inner = if let Some(s) = store {
        KanbanContext::empty(s)
    } else { ... };
    Ok((Self { inner, state_manager }, save_rx, completion_rx))
}
```

KanbanOperations delegation with save queuing via helper:
```rust
fn with_save<F, R>(&mut self, f: F) -> KanbanResult<R>
where F: FnOnce(&mut KanbanContext) -> KanbanResult<R> {
    let result = f(&mut self.inner)?;
    // KanbanContext.execute() already captured undo snapshot internally
    let snapshot = Snapshot::from_context(&self.inner);
    self.state_manager.queue_snapshot(snapshot);
    Ok(result)
}

// Each mutating method becomes a one-liner:
fn create_board(&mut self, name: String, card_prefix: Option<String>) -> KanbanResult<Board> {
    self.with_save(|ctx| ctx.create_board(name, card_prefix))
}

// Read-only methods are direct delegation:
fn list_boards(&self) -> KanbanResult<Vec<Board>> { self.inner.list_boards() }
```

